====Pronunciation====
IPA: ˈkæn.ən

====Homophones====
*[[cannon]]

===Noun===
'''canon''' (plural: [[canons]])

# The books of the Bible officially accepted as holy scripture.
# The complete body of work by an author considered to be authentic.  (''Sherlock Holmes never says, &ldquo;Elementary, my dear Watson.&rdquo; in the canon (i.e. the stories written by Doyle and published in The Strand), but became iconic from its use in theatrical productions.'')
# a generally accepted [[principle]]. (''The trial must proceed according to the canons of law.'')
# a piece of [[music]] in which the same melody is played by different voices, but beginning at different times.
# a religious [[law]] decreed by the church.

